subject: HLTH
title: Foundations of Public Health
description: An introduction to the philosophical, historical, ecological, legislative, and ethical foundations for understanding the practice of public health in Canada. The course is delivered in a 2-week block at the beginning of the MPH program sequence on the UW main campus.  For MPH student only.  The course must be successfully completed by MPH students before proceeding to other courses in the MPH program sequence.
